    "plan_content": "Here is my complete plan. The plan file is at `/Users/timpietrusky/.claude/plans/encapsulated-drifting-bee.md`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nCreates **7 new files** under `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files modified.\n\n### Critical Finding: `getChatChannelMeta` Cannot Be Called with `\"pulseboard\"`\n\n`getChatChannelMeta(id: ChatChannelId)` at `src/channels/chat-meta.ts:126` is a **registry lookup** that only resolves IDs in the hard-coded `CHAT_CHANNEL_ORDER` list of bundled channels. Since \"pulseboard\" is a new fictional channel not in that list, calling `getChatChannelMeta(\"pulseboard\")` would throw at runtime. The plan imports `getChatChannelMeta` per the requirements but constructs the `ChannelMeta` object as a direct literal instead.\n\n---\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Pattern |\n|---|---|\n| `extensions/pulseboard/package.json` | `openclaw` block with label, selectionLabel, docsPath, blurb, setupEntry |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json` | id `\"pulseboard\"`, channels `[\"pulseboard\"]`, empty configSchema — mirrors IRC/Nostr exactly |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts` | 3 interfaces: `PulseBoardAccount` (boardUrl, apiToken, username), `PulseBoardConfig` (accounts map), `PulseBoardMessage` (id, boardId, authorId, content, timestamp) |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>(\"PulseBoard runtime not initialized\")` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime`, `setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin({ base: { id, meta, capabilities, reload, config, setup, gateway, messaging }, outbound })` → exports `pulseBoardPlugin` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry({ id, name, description, plugin, setRuntime })` |\n| `extensions/pulseboard/setup-entry.ts` | `defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n\n### Verification\n- `pnpm tsgo` — type-check all 7 files against SDK contracts\n- `pnpm check` — Oxlint + Oxfmt\n- `pnpm build` — module boundary smoke + no `[INEFFECTIVE_DYNAMIC_IMPORT]` warnings",
